    # 缺口补充: 简答 2
    ("简答","Please explain what you do every day.",None,None,None,None,"My typical day starts at 7 a.m. After getting up, I wash my face and have breakfast. Then I go to university by bus. I have classes from 8 to 12. After lunch, I study at the library or do experiments in the lab from 2 to 5 p.m. In the evening, I have dinner with my roommates. Then I review my lessons or do homework until 10 p.m. Before going to bed at 11, I read books or watch news. Weekends are different - I usually exercise, meet friends, or go shopping.","日常生活",5,"简单"),
    ("简答","Please write a short text about a recent book you read.",None,None,None,None,"I recently finished reading 'The Three-Body Problem' by Liu Cixin. It is a science fiction novel set in a complex universe. The book tells a story about humanity's first contact with an alien civilization. What impressed me most is the author's grand imagination of cosmic sociology and the depth of philosophical questions raised. The characters are vivid, especially Ye Wenjie whose decisions shape humanity's destiny. The book made me think deeply about science, civilization, and our place in the universe. I highly recommend it to anyone interested in deep science fiction.","读后感",5,"中等"),
